Reasearch question

What is the effect of invasive mechanical ventilation (IMV) on overall survival among COVID-19 patients?

Study design

Study design. (A) For 3323 COVID-19 patients, hospitalization records were used for 14 days, starting from the day of hospitalization. Time-dependent variables are L, A, C and Y which were recorded daily. Baseline variables (Bs) contain sociodemographic and comorbidities variables. (B) Two contrasting scenarios correspond to subjects exposed to oxygen supplementation or none at all. On the other hand, the modified treatment policy is a more conservative strategy that avoids the provision of IMV. In both scenarios, the outcome corresponds to death.

Results

Data description

The following graphs and tables are presented below:

  • Sociodemographic: summary of sociodemographic variables separated by patients who presented the event and those who did not in the 14-day period.
